threat_severity.level_description: Severity HIGH because it was considered trojan. Other contributing factor was that it could not be run in sandboxes.

attributes.magic: ELF 32-bit LSB executable, ARM, version 1 (ARM), statically linked, stripped

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: This ELF binary is a malicious IoT botnet agent, likely a variant of the Mirai family or a related strain. It demonstrates classic worm and botnet behaviors, including: 1) Telnet brute-forcing using a large hardcoded list of default credentials (e.g., 'Pon521', 'Zte521', 'vizxv', 'admin', '12345') found in sub_14130. 2) Process discovery and management by scanning /proc to identify competing malware, shells (/bin/sh, /bin/bash), and administrative services (telnetd, sshd) in functions like sub_1208c and sub_83e0. 3) Automated infection and payload delivery via hardcoded shell command templates for wget, tftp, and curl (sub_14130). 4) Network state monitoring by parsing /proc/net/tcp (sub_b8f8). 5) Downloader functionality mimicking Wget (sub_13e60) to fetch additional components via HTTP GET requests for '/dlr.'.
